# Architecture

- Feature-first architecture: each domain owns its module end-to-end.
- No business logic in controllers — delegate to services.
- Services must have single responsibility.
- Use repository pattern for data access (Prisma in repositories only).
- DTO validation on all API inputs (class-validator + Zod in packages/types).
- No circular dependencies between modules or packages.
- Shared types live in `packages/types`; never duplicate domain types.
- Strict TypeScript everywhere — no `any` unless unavoidable.
- Every feature module must be independently testable.
- Long-running work (AI, parsing) goes to BullMQ workers, never blocks API.
